ep in mind economy(Availibility, price), stats, available equipment, hunting areas, territory, and just the size of them. Is it easier to fine a gnome or a troll in a haystack? The troll couldn't even get covered. I'm interested in your all your opinions, but please justify them. Argue away. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=shikkintil>Shik Kintil</A> at: 2/12/01 9:24:31 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cylant>Cylant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/12/01 9:35:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Heres a new one - Races</span><hr size=1> gnomes/halflings with short names.<br>
